webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) In 1745 the work began to expand the medieval church building of the parish in Vist. The new church room was made twice as wide as before by a spread to the north. On the north side, the sacristy also got its place. To the west, the church received as a regular tower and a gunhouse. As early as 1772, however, the tower was damaged at a lightning strike so badly that the spire had to be taken down. The church then stood without a tower to obtain a tower with unusually low hood around 1800 - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000566. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419881. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
